SIMPLE: expert
RECORDS: 3

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Expert
<hw>Ex*pert"</hw> <pr>(⟦ecr⟧ks*p⟦etil⟧rt")</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[F.
<ets>expert</ets>, L. <ets>expertus</ets>, p. p. of <ets>experiri</ets>
to try. See <er>Experience</er>.]</ety> <def>Taught by use, practice, or
experience, experienced; having facility of operation or performance
from practice; knowing and ready from much practice; clever; skillful;
<as>as, an <ex>expert</ex> surgeon; <ex>expert</ex> in chess or
archery.</as></def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>A valiant and most <qex>expert</qex> gentleman.</q>
<rj><qau>Shak.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>What practice, howsoe'er <qex>expert</qex>⟦br⟧
In fitting aptest words to things . . . ⟦br⟧
Hath power to give thee as thou wert?</q>
<rj><qau>Tennyson.</qau></rj></p>

<p><syn><b>Syn.</b> -- Adroit; dexterous; clever; ready;
prompt.</syn>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Expert</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Expert
<hw>Ex"pert</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>An expert
or experienced person; one instructed by experience; one who has skill,
experience, or extensive knowledge in his calling or in any special
branch of learning.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <fld>(Law)</fld> <sd>(a)</sd> <def>A specialist in a
particular profession or department of science requiring for its mastery
peculiar culture and erudition.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><note>⟦hand⟧ Such specialists may be witnesses in matters as to which
ordinary observers could not without such aid form just conclusions, and
are liable for negligence in case they injure another from want of
proper qualifications or proper care in the exercise of their
specialty.</note></p>

<p><sd>(b)</sd> <def>A sworn appraiser.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Expert</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 3 ====
HEADWORD: Expert
<hw>Ex*pert"</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>v. t.</pos> <def>To
experience.</def> <mark>[Obs.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Die would we daily, once it to <qex>expert</qex>.</q>
<rj><qau>Spencer.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Expertly</ent>⟦br⟧
